name: Sandeep Ross Omelette

reviews.review_text: If you are looking for an economical quick snack or a meal.. look no further. Ros omelette is the ideal option. And it is best at Sandeep's in Panaji. The chicken fry is also good. And their fried rice is packed with flavour. You now know where to go when you crave ros omelette üòé

Sort of a legacy place.

Pros:
1. Quick service even when we were there at 1845, few minutes before the official opening.
2. Ross omelette Tastes good for the price paid.
3. The guy running the show is pretty nice and we being early said, ho jayega. Love the phrase.
4. Plenty paid parking nearby.
5. Ample seating via 3 plastic table and chairs.

Cons:
None whatsoever, if you can glance over your typical "vibe", "aura", "aesthetic" pronouns.

Small roadside shop serves authentic Goan savouries. Known for Ross Omelette, tried it and were not disappointed. It was delicious and tasty. The Xacuti Ross is very flavourful. One of the best I have had.
